subject: Baseball
lead_paragraph: Andy Phillips had 48 major league at-bats sprinkled across the last two seasons, barely enough for him to get a feel for what it was like to play for the Yankees. It was definitely not enough time for him to have much of an impact. He was the 25th Yankee, at best, and the 26th Yankee too often.
